In contrast, the President of the Alliance for the Future of Austria (BZ<0xC3><0x96>), the Provincial Governor of Carinthia, J<0xC3><0xB6>rg Haider, is preparing a victorious return to national politics.
According to preliminary results, the Social Democratic Party (SP<0xC3><0x96>) remains the strongest party in the country with 29.8% of the votes, but lost 5.5% of the votes compared to the last elections in 2006.
The <0xC3><0x96>VP was even worse, losing nearly 9% of the vote by 25.6%.
These are the worst results achieved so far by both major parties in Austria’s post-war history, and the result is literally disastrous, especially for the People’s Party, which triggered early elections.
At the beginning of July, when the <0xC3><0x96>VP left the coalition, the EPP had a significant advantage over the SP<0xC3><0x96>, according to opinion polls.
However, the voters apparently punished him for allowing the government to fail.
